00:12:27,958 --> 00:12:30,333
Arati has leveled up in the smartphone era

297
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:32,708
that urge to pull out your phone in an elevator

298
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:35,416
during commercials even in the bathroom

299
00:12:35,458 --> 00:12:36,583
that's her work

300
00:12:36,958 --> 00:12:38,875
the average person now checks their phone

301
00:12:38,875 --> 00:12:42,875
about 150 times a day not because we need to

302
00:12:43,083 --> 00:12:44,458
but because we can't stand

303
00:12:44,458 --> 00:12:46,625
the emptiness of an unoccupied moment

304
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:50,583
Buddha recognized this human tendency

305
00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:53,875
thousands of years ago in the Pali texts

306
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,458
he uses the term abhijappā

307
00:12:56,791 --> 00:12:58,583
a kind of mental restlessness

308
00:12:58,583 --> 00:13:00,375
that prevents peace of mind

